com.lambdaworks.redis.resource

Interface ClientResources

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultClientResources

    public interface ClientResources
    Client Configuration. The client configuration provides heavy-weight resources such as thread pools. ClientResources can be shared across different client instances. Shared instances are not shut down by the client, only dedicated instances are shut down.

    This interface defines the contract. See the DefaultClientResources class for the default implementation.

    The ClientResources instance is stateful. You have to shutdown the instance if you're no longer using it.

    ClientResources provide:
    • An instance of EventLoopGroupProvider to obtain particular EventLoopGroups
    • An instance of EventExecutorGroup for performing internal computation tasks
    Since:
    3.4
    Author:
    Mark Paluch

      • shutdown

        io.netty.util.concurrent.Future<Boolean> shutdown(long quietPeriod,
                                                  long timeout,
                                                  TimeUnit timeUnit)
        Shutdown the ClientResources.
        Parameters:
        quietPeriod - the quiet period as described in the documentation
        timeout - the maximum amount of time to wait until the executor is shutdown regardless if a task was submitted during the quiet period
        timeUnit - the unit of quietPeriod and timeout
        Returns:
        eventually the success/failure of the shutdown without errors.

      • eventLoopGroupProvider

        EventLoopGroupProvider eventLoopGroupProvider()
        Returns the EventLoopGroupProvider that provides access to the particular event loop groups. lettuce requires at least two implementations: NioEventLoopGroup for TCP/IP connections and EpollEventLoopGroup for unix domain socket connections (epoll). You can use DefaultEventLoopGroupProvider as default implementation or implement an own EventLoopGroupProvider to share existing EventLoopGroup's with lettuce.
        Returns:
        the EventLoopGroupProvider which provides access to the particular event loop groups

      • eventExecutorGroup

        io.netty.util.concurrent.EventExecutorGroup eventExecutorGroup()
        Returns the computation pool used for internal operations. Such tasks are periodic Redis Cluster and Redis Sentinel topology updates and scheduling of connection reconnection by ConnectionWatchdog.
        Returns:
        the computation pool used for internal operations

      • ioThreadPoolSize

        int ioThreadPoolSize()
        Returns the pool size (number of threads) for IO threads. The indicated size does not reflect the number for all IO threads. TCP and socket connections (epoll) require different IO pool.
        Returns:
        the pool size (number of threads) for all IO tasks.

      • timer
